 autobiography, resulting in a surprising work that is also uniquely daring.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aFaflak, Joel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFaflak, Joel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266295740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442662957423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442662957.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK